 :tx/rationale "ONLINE CALIBRATION: The chicken-and-egg problem reveals a fundamental architectural issue — the system assumes observation and calibration are separate phases, but concept assignment IS learning. Every observation simultaneously provides data, measures similarity, and generates a calibration signal. The Bayesian posterior after observation N should be the prior for observation N+1, but our system batches the posterior update to harvest time. FIX: Update threshold after EVERY observation using sufficient statistics. Maintain 3 datoms: :calibration/similarity-count (Long), :calibration/similarity-sum (Double), :calibration/similarity-sum-sq (Double). After each observe, add the primary concept's cosine similarity to the running stats, recompute threshold as (mean - 0.5*stddev) which approximates the Otsu split for roughly Gaussian distributions, and write :config/concept.join-threshold. Convergence: by observation 3-5, the threshold is near-optimal. The full Otsu sweep at harvest becomes a refinement, not the primary mechanism. This is ~30 lines in observe.rs. Traces to: ADR-FOUNDATION-031, OBSERVER-4, C9."
